result.execSummary:
The defendant David J. Maszk was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Transfer (>$500 - $5000), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(c).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Preliminary Examination

Defendant David J. Maszk in court with attorney Jessica L. Schuster.  Defendant David J. Maszk in custody.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 14CF23 & 14CF24 @ 10:53 am. Waiver of P.H. examination filed.   Statement of Negotiated plea filed. State agrees with statement. Def. agrees with statement.  Defendant waives right to preliminary hearing on both cases.  Court accepts waiver and finds probable cause on both cases. Informations Filed. 14CF23 Ct 1 Retail Theft,  no contest plea, Ct's 2, 3, & 4 Dismissed consistent w/plea agreement 14CF24 Ct 1 Retail Theft, no contest plea, Ct 2 Possession Drg Paraph, no contest plea, Ct 4 Bailjumping, no contest, ct'2 3, 5 & 6 Dismissed & read in. Def. advised of constitutional rights & J.T. rights. Atty Schuster is satisfied & factual basis.  Court finds pleas are freely & voluntarily given, accepts plea & finds def. Guilty to Retail Theft, ct 1 in 14CF23 & Retail Theft ct 1, Poss Drg Paraph, ct 2 & Bailjumping ct 4 in 14CF24. Def. has nothing to say.
Court accepts plea agreement & orders in 14CF23 ct 1 withheld sentence 2 years probation, Restitution $549.67, joint & several, State has complied w/victim rights. costs &  DNA Surcharge $250.00, 22 days credit if probation revoked.
14CF24 ct 1 withheld sentence 2 years probation, concurrent to 14CF23, Restitution $1474.24, joint & several Counseling, costs, 250 DNA Surcharge,  3 months jail, start today
ct 2 withheld sentence 2 years probation, concurrent with all other probation, counseling & costs, 200 DNA Surcharge
ct 4 withheld sentence 2 years probation, concurrent with all other probation, counseling & costs, 200 DNA surcharge, 22 days credit if probation revoked.
If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.
Huber privileges if employed. DNA Sample. Def. advised of firearm & voting rights. Def. advised of postconviction rights.
Amended Bail/Bond
No contact with Wal-Mart
